        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/{size}/55420_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-18T15:39:47.784Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Groups keep getting full with unknown inactive accounts, and I can‚Äôt keep spamming every person to ask ‚Äòare you still active?‚Äô<br>\nI need a group setting ‚Äòremove inactive members‚Äô .</p>\n<p>details:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>group setting ‚Äúremove inactive members‚Äù</li>\n<li>default for existing group is ‚Äúnever‚Äù</li>\n<li>default for new groups is ‚Äúafter half a year‚Äù<br>\noptions: ‚Äúafter a year, after half a year, after 3 months, after one month, self chosen time‚Äù</li>\n<li>If a user was automatically removed, their group char shows ‚Äúyou were automatically removed due to inactivity‚Äù</li>\n<li>When editing the group setting to a lower timeframe, a warning should be promoted or a delay should be im effect, to prevent accidental mass-kicking group members.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I would define inactive as not having read any messages since. meaning, if you muted or archived a chat and forgot you were in it, you will silently get removed if the set time passes (as that was a choice made by the group admins)</p>\n<p>From a technical and privacy standpoint it would be a mayor privacy compromise to keep collective record of read receipts (and mandate them), as the same record could be used by forensic law enforcement to ‚Äòproof‚Äô that someone was actively aware of the group activity to some extend, or to proof when someone joined the group.</p>\n<p>A way to implement this could be to have clients self-report their inactivity, supplemented with the server kept record of someones last time having any message delivered to them, to also catch users who uninstalled or deactivated their Signal app. I shouldn‚Äôt be an issue that clients could be modified to never self-report inactivity. It‚Äôs not a security feature.</p>\n<p>The feature could also be simplified to only one timeframe, with just a toggle between on or off, if that is easier to implement.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
