        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/kaktusztea/{size}/2576_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-18T17:05:31.509Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think this could be integrated under Group Level Policies.</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"31835\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/kaktusztea/48/2576_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/group-level-policies/31835\">Group level policies</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Now that v2 groups are implemented the admin role, I‚Äôd like to request a feature set that is a part of my earlier proposal for group administration (<a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/technology-preview-signal-private-group-system/10531/25\">link</a>). \nGroup level policies \nThere could be some policy rules that would be applied on every member in the group. \nThese polices would be on/off settings (except the last one) and only admins could set them. \nThis way an admin could customize a group‚Äôs behaviour, profile, purpose, also could prevent to overload big groups i.e by forbidding to post ‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
